 {"id":"frankenpandas-fuzz01","title":"[FUZZ] join_series corpus needs edge case coverage","description":"Extended join_series fuzz corpus from 5 to 17 seeds. Coverage: empty series, duplicate labels, all-null values, null propagation, large overlap, disjoint labels, asymmetric cardinalities, cross product, mixed dtypes, single elements. Also found harness issue: NaN-containing JoinedSeries comparison uses == causing false drift detection (workaround: use Null instead of NaN in seeds). Commit: 06ab9fb","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cc_1","created_at":"2026-04-28T23:45:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cc_1","updated_at":"2026-04-29T00:05:00.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T00:05:00.000000000Z","close_reason":"test(fuzz): 12 join_series edge-case seeds","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenpandas-hll01","title":"[BUG] HyperLogLog::estimate() integer overflow on high rho values","description":"HLL registers can store rho values up to 64 (from leading_zeros()), but estimate() used 2_u32.pow(r) which overflows when r > 31 (panic in debug, wrap in release → incorrect cardinality estimates). Fixed by using 2_f64.powi(). Added test for high rho values. All 66 fp-groupby tests pass. Commit: 2497512","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc_1","created_at":"2026-04-29T00:10:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cc_1","updated_at":"2026-04-29T00:20:00.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T00:20:00.000000000Z","close_reason":"fix(fp-groupby): HyperLogLog integer overflow","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
